element_texts.text:
[letterhead: Hotel Lanier, Macon, GA]
Dear John

    How lovely + decent of you to write - about Will [?]. I had thought it did something I wanted it to do.

    A low tone - [?] found in the [?] - like a fan dancer - 

    I am trying to make a long novel that way - in different keys - things beating on the consciousness of a young man - 
    
    I hope - [?] - first - to make the new one express the whole movement. Its a nice challenge.

    I think Faulkner's difficulty is [ahead?]. I saw him at

Charlottesville + told him that. They'll make an ass of him if they can, playing with him, boosting him.

    Then de-pose him for a new man.

    This is the difficulty - to ride through that + forget it.

    Bob has taken over the apt. with his new wife. John has a room in [?] Alley and I have a nice house that looks out on our lovely hill. I'll not be here much. I plan to go to Europe this summer.

    As Always

    Sherwood Anderson
